함께 올려도 좋다.\n\n\n[ Abalone viscera cream pasta ]\n\n[ Ingredients ]\n\n*Cleaning the abalone\n4 abalones\n1L water\n\n*Abalone viscera cream sauce\nEntire abalone viscera\n1 carton (200ml) milk\n1/2 (125g) onion\n5 (about 30g) whole bulbs of garlic\n3 tbsp (21g) cooking oil\nsome flavored salt\n\n*Abalone viscera cream pasta\n160g (80g pre-cooking) cooked spaghetti noodles\n20g (about 2 tbsp) butter\n1 and 1/4 tbsp (10g) parmesan cheese powder\nentire cleaned abalone flesh\nentire abalone viscera cream sauce\n1 stalk (about 10g) scallion\n\n[ Directions ]\n1. Clean the abalone with an abalone brush.\n   *If you do not have an abalone brush, you can use a toothbrush instead.\n2. In a pot, bring the water to a boil. Add the abalones and blanch for about 3 minutes. Then, let the abalones cool down in cold water.\n   * The cooking time may vary depending on the size of the abalone.\n3. Using a spoon, deshell the blanched abalones. Then, make two vertical slits on the surface where the shell was on, and slice the abalones horizontally to pieces 0.5cm thick.\n4. In a frying pan, add cooking oil, onion, garlic, and blanched abalone viscera, and stir-fry over medium heat until the ingredients are just about to burn.\n   *If you prefer, you can remove the gizzard, which is the protruding part of the viscera.\n5. In a blender, blend the milk, stir-fried vegetables and viscera, and flavored salt to make abalone viscera cream sauce.\n   *If you are using fresh cream, half the milk and add the fresh cream with the pasta noodles.\n6. In a frying pan, add some cooking oil and cook the abalone flesh.\n6. Add the abalone viscera cream sauce. When the sauce comes to a boil, add in the spaghetti noodles and butter and bring to a boil, stirring as you go.\n7. Once the sauce comes to a boil, add the spaghetti and butter and stir as it cooks.\n   *If you are using fresh cream, now is the time to add it in.\n   *If it tastes bland, season with salt.\n   *Keep in mind that we will be adding parmesan cheese powder later as the cheese is also seasoned.\n8. Stir in the parmesan cheese powder and when the cream gets thick, turn off the heat.\n9. Plate and garnish with sliced scallion.\n   *You can decorate with a cleanly washed abalone shell filled with abalone flesh.\n\n\n\n한식을 사랑하는 외국인분들을 위해 외국어 자막을 첨부하였습니다.\n본 영상의 자막은 통합 언어 플랫폼 ‘플리토’와 함께 합니다.\nSubtitles in foreign languages are provided for everyone who loves Korean food.\nAll subtitles are provided by an integrated language platform, Flitto.\nhttps://www.flitto.com/pro/caption-tr...','고급 레스토랑 따라잡기! 전복 내장 이렇게 드시면 정말 맛있어요~ 전복크림파스타'),(644,'/watch?v=9r2lUaCZmK8','#백종원 #라이브 #만두\n만두에 마라소스 찍어서 드셔보셨나요?\n매콤함과 감칠맛이 폭발하는 조합!\n너무 맛있어서 꼭 한번 해보시라고, 인스타 라이브를 해봤습니다.\n\n혹시 여러분만의 만두 꿀조합이 있다면 댓글로 알려주세요!\n\n\n한식을 사랑하는 외국인분들을 위해 외국어 자막을 첨부하였습니다.\n본 영상의 자막은 통합 언어 플랫폼 ‘플리토’와 함께 합니다.\nSubtitles in foreign languages are provided for everyone who loves Korean food.\nAll subtitles are provided by an integrated language platform, Flitto.\nhttps://www.flitto.com/pro/caption-tr...','만두를 맛있게 먹는 또 다른 방법? 매운맛 좋아하는 분들 따라해보세요 [인스타 라이브 편집본]'),(645,'/watch?v=b2AXKI76rKI','#백종원 #마라감자 #스푸파\n저희 회사에서 \'만능마라소스\'가 새로 출시되었습니다~!\n\n팀원분들이 마라소스 활용법을 많이 요청하셔서\n\'스트리트 푸드 파이터 청두 편\'에서 먹었던 마라감자를 만들어봤어요\n일단 시~원한 맥주?부터 준비하고 시작하세요!\n\n=============================\n\n[ 마라감자 ]\n\n[ 재료 ]\n냉동감자 200g\n식용유 1/4컵(40g)\n마라소스 약 1과 1/2큰술(25g)\n대파 1/5대(20g)\n\n[ 만드는 법 ]\n1. 대파는 두께 0.3cm로 송송 썰어 준비한다. \n2. 프라이팬에 식용유를 두른 후 강불에 예열한다.\n3. 냉동감자를 넣고 전체적으로 노릇노릇해질 때까지 튀기듯이 굽는다.\n4. 감자가 튀겨지면 기름을 따라낸 후 대파를 넣고 볶는다.\n5. 불을 중불로 줄인 후 마라소스를 넣고 골고루 섞어 완성한다.\n   *감자튀김의 색이 너무 진하거나 프라이팬에 열이 너무 쎈 경우에는 불을 끄고 섞는다.\n\n[ Mala potatoes ]\n\n[ Ingredients ]\n200g frozen potatoes\n1/4 cup (40g) cooking oil\nabout 1 and 1/2 tbsp (25g) mala sauce\n1/5 stalk (20g) green onion\n\n[ Directions ]\n1. Chop the green onion into slices 0.3cm thick.\n2. In a frying pan, preheat the cooking oil over high heat.\n3. Add the frozen potatoes and fry in deep-frying style until they turn golden.\n4. When the 