 프라이팬에 기름을 두르고 달걀을 넣어 프라이를 한 후 완성된 볶음밥 위에 올려 마무리한다.\n\n\nChinese Fried Rice\n\n[Ingredients]\n\nRice 1 bowl (200g)\n2 eggs (120g)\nGreen onion 1/2 cup (40g)\nCarrot 1/4 cup (20g)\n1/4 onion (50g)\nDark soy sauce 1 tbsp (10g)\nCooking oil 4 tbsp (40g)\nSesame oil 1/3 tbsp (2g)\nMSG 1/4 tbsp (2g)\nSalt 1g\n\n\n[Directions]\n\n1. Chop carrot and onion. Slice green onion in half and chop finely.\n2. Add cooking oil and egg to the frying pan make scrambled eggs.\n3. Once the egg is cooked half-way, set it aside and stir-fry the carrot, onion, and green onion on one side.\n4. When the vegetables become golden brown, mix with the scrambled eggs and set them aside.\n5. Add soy sauce to the part without oil and let it boil.\n6. Once the soy sauce starts to burn, turn off the heat and mix with the scrambled eggs and the vegetables.\n7. Once all the ingredients are mixed, add salt and rice and mix, then stir-fry over high heat.\n8. Season to taste, add MSG and finish with sesame oil.\n\n-------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\nFried rice with pork belly\n\n[Ingredients]\n\nRice 1 bowl (200g)\nPork belly 100g\nGreen onion 1/2 cup (40g)\nCarrot 1/4 cup (20g)\nCooking oil 1 tbsp (10g) \nDark soy sauce 1 tbsp (10g)\n1 egg (60g)\nSalt 1g\n\n[Directions]\n\n1. Chop green onion and slice carrot finely.\n2. Cut pork belly vertically in small pieces.\n3. Add a little bit of cooking oil to the frying pan, and stir-fry the pork belly.\n4. When the fat from pork belly oozes out, add the carrot and stir-fry.\n5. Once the carrot is cooked half way, stir-fry the green onion and mix with the pork belly.\n6. Set the ingredients aside, add the soy sauce to the part without oil and let it boil.\n7. Mix the burnt soy sauce with the vegetables and pork belly, turn off the heat, and add salt.\n8. Add the rice, mix with the ingredients, and stir-fry over high heat.\n9. Make a fried egg in the same frying pan and put it on top of the fried rice.\n\n\n한식을 사랑하는 외국인분들을 위해 외국어 자